                <note rend="inline" type="source">441.11 W 892/43: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Houghton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-04-14T11:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 14, 1926—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 14—9:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>73. Chamberlain tells me he has cabled Howard to the effect that he is in
                    sympathy with informal investigation of claims situation provided this can be
                    carried on in Washington and without publicity. His attitude is much more
                    conciliatory.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Houghton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
